	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				It's all preference, and style until 50+  Otherwise, really just has to do with your style.  Personally, I love having high INT and STR to match it, I sacrifice a bit of AC, NOT MUCH, but a bit, for mana.  It's been a hard life maintaining 170INT as an SK and keeping my AC at bay wiht 850AC at level 44, but it works great.  As for umbral, well I don't like it much, I can't wear it yet, so counteract me, call me stupid etc.  But I would rather have that incredible AC difference in Blood Ember, that would make tanking just that much better, lower my INT to 165, but i can live with that.  Reason AC is so much nicer to boost than attributes is becuase AC is much harder to boost than your attributes.  At that high of a level you got shamans that have incrediable stat boost, you have enchanters that give clarity, you have druids giving out even more stat boost, then there is teh cleric with real good AC boosts, but does it compare, numberwise to the stat boosts?  No, not as much AC is it?  That's my logic.  As for HP, well we all have about the same as a class give or take about 250hp depending on race/stamina.  And were one has lots more HP, the other has lots more INT to lifedraw that much back.  Just my opinion on the matter.  Take care all!<BR>
<BR>
44SK Teir'Dal
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
