	<tr>
		
			<td colspan="2" bgcolor="#DEDACB" background="http://www.everlore.com/gimages/tb_beige.gif">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				Well, I dunno here, Sage says Blood Ember is better but then he says it has 5 more ac...well I'm pretty sure Umbral has 17ac making the difference between them 4ac.<BR>
That aside, I think people freak out about AC way too much. They beef it up to the exclusion of everything else...IMHO Umbral is better as it adds considerable stats in addition to great AC. That 35hps may not seem like much, but the more hps you have, the more efficient a clerics CH becomes. In addition, that 10 sv magic will often times be the difference between a krupp shaman landing his turgurs on you or you resisting. To further this argument, most shadow knights I have seen use umbral helm(at higher lvls). Don't get me wrong, AC is very important, just don't ignore that their are other factors.<BR>
<BR>
Den, 55th war, Torv
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
